Chief Executive Officer of Akamai Technologies (NASDAQ:AKAM), Leighton F Thomson, buys 19,817 shares worth $999,768
According to Akamai Technologies's most recent Form 4 filing with the SEC dated Jul 17 08:20 AM, company Chief Executive Officer, Leighton F Thomson disclosed buying 19,817 shares at a cost of $50.45. At the time of this transaction (Jul 14), this trade was worth $999,768 in total. As of Jul 14, Leighton F Thomson now owns 3,326,715 shares in total worth about $168,398,313.3. 
For the last few recent trades made by Akamai Technologies (NASDAQ:AKAM) Chief Executive Officer, Leighton F Thomson, we have the following information:




SEC Form 4 filing: Jun 15: Bought 20,397 shares at the rate of $49.02 per share. Total worth of this trade was $999,861. Total number of shares owned as of Jun 15 were 247,454
SEC Form 4 filing: May 31: Bought 21,196 shares at the rate of $47.17 per share. Total worth of this trade was $999,815. Total number of shares owned as of May 31 were 227,057
SEC Form 4 filing: Dec 15: Bought 14,828 shares at the rate of $67.43 per share. Total worth of this trade was $999,852. Total number of shares owned as of Dec 15 were 3,142,184




