Akamai Technologies Inc (AKAM) CEO F Thomson Leighton Bought $999,861 of Shares


June 16, 2017, 07:15:04 PM EDT
By insider, GuruFocus









































Shutterstock photo


CEO of Akamai Technologies Inc ( AKAM ) F Thomson Leighton bought 20,397 shares of AKAM on 06/15/2017 at an average price of $49.02 a share. The total cost of this purchase was $999,861.Akamai Technologies Inc provides cloud services for delivering, optimizing and securing online content and business applications. The Company's sales and service professionals are located in more than 50 offices in the United States, Europe and Asia. Akamai Technologies Inc has a market cap of $8.56 billion; its shares were traded at around $49.50 with a P/E ratio of 27.05 and P/S ratio of 3.66. Akamai Technologies Inc had annual average EBITDA growth of 17.00% over the past ten years. GuruFocus rated Akamai Technologies Inc the business predictability rank of 5-star .CEO Recent Trades:CEO F Thomson Leighton bought 20,397 shares of AKAM stock on 06/15/2017 at the average price of $49.02. The price of the stock has increased by 0.98% since.CEO F Thomson Leighton bought 21,196 shares of AKAM stock on 05/31/2017 at the average price of $47.17. The price of the stock has increased by 4.94% since.Directors and Officers Recent Trades:Director Paul Sagan sold 17,889 shares of AKAM stock on 06/14/2017 at the average price of $49.53. The price of the stock has decreased by 0.06% since.click here

.About GuruFocus: GuruFocus.com tracks the stocks picks and portfolio holdings of the world's best investors. This value investing site offers stock screeners and valuation tools. And publishes daily articles tracking the latest moves of the world's best investors. GuruFocus also provides promising stock ideas in 3 monthly newsletters sent to Premium Members . 

